message: Hello! I'm interested in trading and hope we can find mutually beneficial deals. I'm willing to negotiate fairly and consistently across all rounds. What's your general approach to pricing?
I'm looking for profitable trades. My pricing will be competitive but needs to cover my costs. Let's see what price range works for both of us.
I bid 25 last round but your ask of 67 was too high. I can go higher if you can come down - let's try to meet somewhere in the middle range.
I appreciate the willingness to negotiate. I can come down some, but need at least mid-40s to make it worthwhile. What's your best offer?
My maximum is in the high 30s. Can you work with something in that range instead of mid-40s?
High 30s is below my cost threshold. I need at least 42 to make any profit. Can you stretch to 40? Otherwise we'll both miss out on potential gains.
We're very close! My bid was 37, your ask was 40 - just 3 apart. I can meet you at 39 if you can ask 39. That gives us both decent profit and gets us trading.
That sounds fair! I'm willing to ask 39 if you bid 39. Let's start trading consistently and both profit from this arrangement.
We agreed on 39/39 last round but I bid 38 and you asked 39. Let me correct that - I'll bid exactly 39 this round if you ask exactly 39 as we discussed.
Perfect! I'll ask exactly 39 this round as agreed. Let's execute this trade and continue this profitable arrangement for the remaining rounds.

I'll bid 37 for all remaining rounds. At 38 I only break even. You still profit +3 at 37. Let's trade consistently at 37/37 so we both benefit rather than miss more trades.
